<dl id="n36084d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36084d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36084d"> 84(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cut son in two</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Beside the larger monument is a smaller one bearing a half-length effigy in Purbeck marble. This figure is generally believed to represent Strongbow&apos;s son, whom his father is said to have <mark>cut in two</mark> for cowardice in battle <small> Samuel A. Ossory Fitzpatrick, <a name="SAOF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SAOF"><cite title="source">Dublin: A Historical and Topographical Account of the City</cite></a> (1907) 22</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
